Former Australian radio host Mel Greig has revealed her personal torment over the prank which resulted in the suicide of a nurse in London in an interview with BBC2.

Returning to radio for the first time since she and fellow 2Day FM co-host Michael Christian posed as the Queen and Prince Charles as part of a prank in 2012 to gain information about the Duchess of Cambridge following the birth of Prince George.

Jacintha Saldana was the nurse who took the call, taking her life two days later and blaming her decision on the actions of the Australian radio hosts.

